"Raes N., Mols J.B., Willemse L.P.M., Smets E.F.","Georeferencing specimens by combining digitized maps with SRTM digital elevation data and satellite images: A Bornean case study",2009,"Blumea: Journal of Plant Taxonomy and Plant Geography","54","1-3",,"162","165",,,10.3767/000651909X475950,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-70350413632&partnerID=40&md5=961c25838c1e96ae1c9a7f64a05fa549","National Herbarium of the Netherlands, Leiden University branch, P.O. Box 9514, 2300 RA Leiden, Netherlands; Laboratory of Plant Systematics, Institute of Botany and Microbiology, Kasteelpark Arenberg 31, B-3001 Leuven, Belgium","Raes, N., National Herbarium of the Netherlands, Leiden University branch, P.O. Box 9514, 2300 RA Leiden, Netherlands; Mols, J.B., National Herbarium of the Netherlands, Leiden University branch, P.O. Box 9514, 2300 RA Leiden, Netherlands; Willemse, L.P.M., National Herbarium of the Netherlands, Leiden University branch, P.O. Box 9514, 2300 RA Leiden, Netherlands; Smets, E.F., National Herbarium of the Netherlands, Leiden University branch, P.O. Box 9514, 2300 RA Leiden, Netherlands, Laboratory of Plant Systematics, Institute of Botany and Microbiology, Kasteelpark Arenberg 31, B-3001 Leuven, Belgium","For numerous scientific purposes collection records need to be georeferenced. Although the geographic coordinates of many of the collection localities are available in gazetteers, especially collections from tropical areas of the world are still not georeferenced. In an attempt to georeference these localities for Indonesian Borneo we used digitized old maps which were georegistered with SRTM digital elevation data, and Landsat 7- and JERS-1 SAR radar satellite images. This enabled us to georeference 2 577 additional collections from Indonesian Borneo, belonging to 1 744 taxa, which were collected at 134 previously not georeferenced localities. This applied methodology enables researchers to georeference their historical collections for biodiversity, biogeographical, and global climate change impact studies. © 2009 Nationaal Herbarium Nederland.","Borneo; Georeferencing; Georegistration; Historical map; JERS-1 SAR; Landsat; SRTM digital elevation data",,,,,,,"Aiba, S.-I., Kitayama, K., Repin, R., Species composition and species-area relationships of trees in nine permanent plots in altitudinal sequences on different geological substrates of Mount Kinabalu (2002) Sabah Parks Nature Journal, 5, pp. 7-69; Ashton, P.S., Lambir's forest: The world's most diverse known tree assemblage? (2005) Pollination ecology and the rain forest: Sarawak studies, pp. 191-216. , In: DW Roubik, Sakai S, Hamid Karim AA (eds), Springer, New York; Ashton, P.S., Hall, P., Comparisons of structure among mixed dipterocarp forests of north-western Borneo (1992) The Journal of Ecology, 80, pp. 459-481; Buys, D.W., Witkamp, H., Endert, F.H., Siebers, H.C., Bosch, D.F.K., (1927) Midden-Oost-Borneo expeditie 1925, , Kolff & Co., Weltevreden; Dalton, B., (1978) Indonesia handbook, , second edition. Moon Publications, London; Dunselman, J., Aantekeningen over zandpadangs in Borneo's Wester-afdeeling (1939) De Tropische Natuur, 28, pp. 71-82; Endert, F.H., De proefbaanmetingen in Sangkoelirang (Z.O. Borneo) (1933), 26, pp. 50-92Graham, C.H., Ferrier, S., Huettman, F., Moritz, C., Peterson, A.T., New developments in museum-based informatics and applications in biodiversity analysis (2004) Trends in Ecology, Evolution, 19, pp. 497-503; Hallier, H., Rapport over de botanische tochten in Borneo's Westerafdeling gedurende de Borneo-expeditie 1893-94 (1895) Natuurkundig Tijdschrift, 54, pp. 406-449; Hortal, J., Lobo, J.M., Jiménez-Valverde, A., Limitations of biodiversity databases: Case study on seed-plant diversity in Tenerife, Canary Islands (2007) Conservation Biology, 21, pp. 853-863; Kennedy, M., (2000) Understanding map projections, , Environmental Systems Research Institute, Inc., Redlands, USA; Moerman, D.E., Estabrook, G.F., The bota